features: Lightweight carry-on bag with a sturdy frame design and bottom molded tray for structural stability. Meets carry-on size restrictions for most domestic airlines.
4-wheel dual airplane-style smooth rolling and 360-degree spinning system, lightweight handle with aluminum handle system for easy maneuvering, and double tubes to maximize interior space.
Expandable up to 2 inches for maximum packing capacity with low profile carry handles, two exterior compartments, interior lid pocket, side pocket, and adjustable hold down straps.
Fully lined with multiple zip pockets and tie-down straps to keep belongings secure.
Dimensions: 22" x 13.5" x 8.5" + 2" depth gusset, Packing Dimensions: 18.5" x 13" x 8" + 2" depth gusset, Weight: 8 lb., Linear Dimensions: 44 in, 2-year warranty.
body.description: Traveler's Choice's Lares Luggage Collection is made of super-light yet durable polyester fabric, with multiple front pockets, aluminum push-lock telescopic handle, 360-degree wheel system provide maximum protection, comfort and mobility enhance your travel experiences. Aluminum handle system allows you to maneuver your bag with ease. The double tubes of the handle system maximize interior space for packing. Dual airplane-style smooth rolling and 360-degree spinning wheel system. Expansion gusset boosts extra packing capacity by 2 inches or up to 25%. Fully lined imprinted interior with multiple zip pockets & two tie-down straps. Large front opening zipper pocket for easy access to travel necessities. Top and side carry handles make for easy lifting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This bag is fantastic, it stretches beyond belief. I am a fat girl and went away for 2 weeks and packed 3 pairs of shoes, fat girl clothes for 2 weeks, undergarments, toiletries, a hair dryer and straightening iron and I still had room to bring back souvenirs. This suitcase is very well made and you will not be disappointed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Very useful and as described. Also a very cheery color and love the blue interior.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seems bigger on inside than outside.
reviews.reviewText: I really like this suitcase. It’s about an inch smaller all around than my old one but, it’s definitely deeper. It can be expanded even more by unzipping zippers that run parallel to the opening and closing zippers. I love that there are four wheels which makes for easy maneuvering with one hand. I highly recommend this suitcase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not as durable as I thought it would be
reviews.reviewText: I've used it four times and itis now starting to come apart in the main zipper area. The zipper is pulling apart at the bottom of the suitcase. It is still useable for road trips but cannot be used on airline travel.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice and roomy but not well balanced
reviews.reviewText: Liked the suitcase but the wheels are too high and it is tippy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Poor quality & service
reviews.reviewText: The small one ripped at the seam before it ever saw an airplane. Literally first use and it has a tear. I sincerely hope the company does the right thing and replaces the defective suitcase. Will report back after I hear from the company.Update: the company has not gotten back to me in response to my complaint about a rip in the fabric before we even used the luggage. Now we've used the medium one on a 3 week trip. The luggage did not perform well in Europe. The wheels are ok at best and the bag itself is pretty worn, especially in comparison to the other higher quality piece of luggage we used. I wouldn't buy again
